Date: 0/0/1853
Source: Flora NZ
Author: HOOKER
Vol / Page:  I Flowering Plants 230
Edition:
Quote: Fagus <i>Solandri,</i> Hook. fil. ... English name, `White Birch', <i>Bidwill</i>. A very beautiful lofty evergreen tree, attaining 100 feet in deep rich soil ... <i>Old bark </i>black, cracked; young white, smooth, like [English] Birch, which the wood also resembles, being close, tough, white, not durable under exposure ...
Notes:

